<L>__{interior bridge}
<A>__{john, suited up, heads for the open front hatch when he spots will sitting alone in the com chair, tinkering with his deck.}
<C>__{john}
<D>__{aren't you coming out to say goodbye?}
<A>__{will just shakes his head.}
<C>__{will}
<D>__{you're always leaving. what if...}
<A>__{will looks away, finally giving voice to his worst fear.}
<C>__{will}
<D>__{what if one time you don't come home...}
<A>__{john stares at his son, unsure what to say, the boy's anguish so deep and apparent. he reaches into his shirt, takes off his dog tags.}
<C>__{john}
<D>__{whenever your grandfather went away on a mission, held leave these with me. for safe keeping. and when he got home i d always be waiting to give them back.}
<A>__{he lifts the chain and places it around the boy's neck.}
<C>__{john}
<D>__{i'm coming back will. i promise.}
<A>__{will is silent. john touches the boy's hair, then walks out. a beat. will looks up after his father, fingering the dog tags.}
